Slang. A hybrid of the words "Japanese" and "English."
Used by Japanese-Americans or Japanese expats and exchange students.
Refers to English words that have been co-opted into Japanese vernacular, often incorrectly.
Also, English terms or names that have been localized for Japanese use.

Examples:
"Ken-Ta" for Kentucky Fried Chicken
"Sta-Ba" for Starbucks Coffee
"Morning Service" for Breakfast

Numerous examples can be found on parody site: www.engrish.com